full_text: @josephjefe Where in the #nflverse does snap data live?

Weekly snap counts including the division game, and our second bye of the season!! Starting with tight ends, as always, because there's not much to talk about with them. It's Kelce, and Gray gets a nice 50% of the snaps too. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/Mxo26IYEEf

Wide receivers!! Moore's snaps are right in line with where he was pre-injury, after dropping from a midseason high. Our favorite #2 WR still garnering #2 WR snaps, so that's something. Toney is INCREDIBLY efficient while getting Skyy Moore level snaps. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/UGVclbbr5x

Running Backs! McKinnon got more run this week, probably because they valued his consistency at pass blocking after Mahomes was injured. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/amrqIOJHWK

On to defense!! Cornerbacks first. Watson continuing his takeover from Williams that started right after the first Cincy game. Sneed and McDuffie just out there playing ball all day. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/NSYVdXSa9j

Safeties next. Hard to see, but Thornhill and Reid are both at 100% of the snaps.  Reid is just hiding behind Thornhill on this chart. Cook is the only other safety getting any snaps at all. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/aUnfd2IIl4

Linebackers!! Everyone's favorite role player, Darius Harris, saw his snaps drop this week, as did Chenal. Gay saw a corresponding rise in snap percentages. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/80Pe6gA0SM

Interior defensive line. Chris Jones saw his snap percentages rise again, while everyone else saw theirs drop. Hope he's got two more 80%+ days in him this year. He's been insane so far. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/FYISQsRenj
